headline: Authorities face security and accommodation challenges ahead of Brazil's COP30
description: Doubts over whether the police can handle the Brazilian event have surfaced after deadly raids in Rio de Janeiro. Meanwhile, accommodation prices have dropped, but 49 countries are reportedly still searching for lodging.

headline: Charles Coste, world's oldest living Olympic champion, dies at 101
description: The former French cyclist, a gold medalist in the team pursuit at the 1948 London Games, carried the Olympic flame during the opening ceremony of the Paris 2024 Games. He died on Thursday at the age of 101.

headline: Rosalía returns with mystical album: 'God has given me so much, the least I could do is make an album for him'
description: Three albums and a string of hit singles have propelled her to the ranks of global pop divas. After a three-year hiatus, the 33-year-old Catalan artist returns with 'Lux,' a musical fresco in praise of the divine and major female saints.

headline: France's new 'unproductive wealth' tax reflects a limited adjustment
description: MPs approved on Friday a modification of the real estate wealth tax. Its base was broadened, but the tax rate was reduced by a third for the very wealthy. Its yield remains unclear.
